ortItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534074\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534074\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yfw1665702779974.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yfw1665702779974.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yfw1665702779974.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yfw1665702779974\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Resource Browser\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__resource_browser_20519\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Every standard editor has a Resource Browser that enables you to find the resources such as templates, objects, and snippets, that you want to use in the current context. You use these resources to create and insert new objects and to help you write code.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__p_d5111e1_d5112e1_d5113e1\">The resources that are available depend on the current editor and worksheet. For example:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2093e1_d2094e1_d2095e1\">In the Project Editor, there is only one worksheet and its Resource Browser has tabs which list:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2096e1_d2097e1_d2098e1\">Templates for creating new main development objects\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2099e1_d2100e1_d2101e1\">Modeled components for creating derived components\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2102e1_d2103e1_d2104e1\">Existing main development objects that can be added to the project\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2105e1_d2106e1_d2107e1\">Imported database table definitions for creating new modeled entities\n </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2108e1_d2109e1_d2110e1\">In the Entity Editor, the Resource Browser of each worksheet lists different resources. In the Define Structure worksheet, it lists templates for creating fields and subtype entities, but in the Define Relationships worksheet it lists modeled entities so you can choose the one with which to create a new relationship.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2111e1_d2112e1_d2113e1\">In the Component Editor, the Define Structure worksheet provides templates for non-database objects, and modeled entities and fields for creating derived objects in your new component.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2114e1_d2115e1_d2116e1\">In the Write Script worksheet of the Entity Editor, Component Editor and the Library editors, it lists the contents of snippet libraries, so that you can copy and paste code snippets into your script modules or layout.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__p_d5114e1_d5115e1_d5116e1\">You can search and filter the contents of the Resource Browser by entering text in its U-Bar or using its context menu, and select an object to copy or insert it in the worksheet editor, either by dragging and dropping it or by using the context menu.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__topic_d2572e1_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1_d2576e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d320486e93\">\n                  \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2117e1_d2118e1_d2119e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yed1704964703330.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yed1704964703330.html\" title=\"The number of objects available for selection in the Resource Browser may be very large, so you can filter the content in a variety of ways, depending on context.\">Filter and Search for Objects in Resource Browser</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2120e1_d2121e1_d2122e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"flj1690357335479.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/flj1690357335479.html\" title=\"You can select templates, modeled objects, and code snippets in the Resource Browser and add them to current object. You can drag and drop objects, or use the context menu.\">Add Objects from the Resource Browser</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2123e1_d2124e1_d2125e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kif1665702780045.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kif1665702780045.html\" title=\"You can select multiple objects in a Resource Browser, Structure Editor, or Properties Inspector using Windows mouse key conventions Ctrl+Click and Shift+Click.\">Select Multiple Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__fig_d5120e1_d5121e1_d5122e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Templates Tab in the Resource Browser of the Project Editor</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Resource Browser of Project Editor\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/rb_prj.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2126e1_d2127e1_d2128e1\">Tabs show different categories of objects that you can select and use.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yfw1665702779974__li_d2129e1_d2130e1_d2131e1\">Some tabs contain a U-Bar in the Resource Browser that enables you to browse and select specific objects.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534074\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534074\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Resource Browser Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Resource Browser Every standard editor has a Resource Browser that enables you to find the resources such as templates, objects, and snippets, that you want to use in the current context. You use these resources to create and insert new objects and to help you write code. The resources that are available depend on the current editor and worksheet. For example: In the Project Editor, there is only one worksheet and its Resource Browser has tabs which list: Templates for creating new main development objects Modeled components for creating derived components Existing main development objects that can be added to the project Imported database table definitions for creating new modeled entities In the Entity Editor, the Resource Browser of each worksheet lists different resources. In the Define Structure worksheet, it lists templates for creating fields and subtype entities, but in the Define Relationships worksheet it lists modeled entities so you can choose the one with which to create a new relationship. In the Component Editor, the Define Structure worksheet provides templates for non-database objects, and modeled entities and fields for creating derived objects in your new component. In the Write Script worksheet of the Entity Editor, Component Editor and the Library editors, it lists the contents of snippet libraries, so that you can copy and paste code snippets into your script modules or layout. You can search and filter the contents of the Resource Browser by entering text in its U-Bar or using its context menu, and select an object to copy or insert it in the worksheet editor, either by dragging and dropping it or by using the context menu. How to Filter and Search for Objects in Resource Browser Add Objects from the Resource Browser Select Multiple Objects Figure 1. Templates Tab in the Resource Browser of the Project Editor Tabs show different categories of objects that you can select and use. Some tabs contain a U-Bar in the Resource Browser that enables you to browse and select specific objects. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}